Spain's Minas de Almaden y Arrayanes S.A.Said it will host a conference of mercury producers here at theend of April to study how to stimulate low mercury prices.    Last week, Almaden and Algerian producer ENOF agreed toestablish a minimum price of 300 dlrs per flask (34.5 kilos)for spot mercury sales, up from the previous minimum of 240dlrs.    A Minas de Almaden statement said the non-communist world'smain mercury producers had decided not to sign any contractsusing the reference price of specialist publications, becauseit was well below their costs of production. REUTER&#3;